content:
Add Contact Requests to Experience Cloud Sites

In Experience Builder, add a contact request flow to your Experience Cloud site so site members can request that customer support contact them.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
User permissions needed: View Setup and Configuration AND Create and Set Up Experiences.

Create a contact request flow before adding it to your site. IMPORTANT: Ensure site users have the Run Flows permission, including the Guest User profile.

Add one of the following components:

* Contact Request Button & Flow—Users click a button and detail their issue in a popup form.
* Flow—Your flow is embedded in the page.

Specify the contact request flow in the component's properties. Only active screen flows are supported. Customize the button label and styling if desired.

Save and publish your changes.

SEE ALSO: Experience Builder Component: Contact Request Button & Flow, Edit Pages and Components in Experience Builder.
title: Adding Contact Requests to Experience Cloud Sites
